4Ô∏è‚É£ Issues Faced, Mistakes & Questions Asked
‚ùå Issue 1: Unable to Edit server.xml
Error:
E505: "/etc/tomcat/server.xml" is read-only
Cause:
‚Ä¢	File opened without proper write permissions
Solution:
‚Ä¢	Reopened file using root privileges:
‚Ä¢	sudo vi /etc/tomcat/server.xml
________________________________________
‚ùå Issue 2: Confusion About Tomcat Configuration Path
Question Asked:
‚ÄúFrom whereis tomcat, how do I know where server.xml is?‚Äù
Cause:
‚Ä¢	Multiple Tomcat-related directories returned
Solution:
‚Ä¢	Identified /etc/tomcat as configuration directory
‚Ä¢	Confirmed presence of server.xml using ls and find
________________________________________
‚ùå Issue 3: Confusion Between /usr/share/tomcat/conf and /etc/tomcat
Question Asked:
‚ÄúHow can I open conf?‚Äù
Cause:
‚Ä¢	conf is a directory, not a file
‚Ä¢	RHEL-based systems separate config and application files
Solution:
‚Ä¢	Used cd to enter directory
‚Ä¢	Learned that /etc/tomcat is the active config location
________________________________________
‚ùå Issue 4: Concern About Running Tomcat as Root
Question Asked:
‚ÄúTomcat should be run by a user, not by root, right?‚Äù
Clarification:
‚Ä¢	Root is used only for installation and configuration
‚Ä¢	Tomcat service runs as tomcat user via systemd
Verification:
ps -ef | grep tomcat
‚úî Security best practice followed
________________________________________
‚ùå Issue 5: Understanding systemctl start vs enable
Question Asked:
‚ÄúWhat do these commands do?‚Äù
Clarification:
‚Ä¢	start ‚Üí starts service immediately
‚Ä¢	enable ‚Üí ensures service starts on reboot
‚úî Correct usage confirmed
________________________________________
